so I sort of got one of everything.

29:32.679 --> 29:34.427
[Noah] What the...?

29:34.428 --> 29:36.053
How did we...?

29:38.133 --> 29:39.733
What are we doing here?

29:39.734 --> 29:42.344
It was an honor and a privilege

29:42.345 --> 29:44.803
to watch you work.

29:44.804 --> 29:48.135
We're like Kerouac and Burroughs.

29:48.136 --> 29:49.281
Who's who, do you think?

29:49.282 --> 29:50.761
I mean, obviously you're Kerouac.

29:50.762 --> 29:52.344
But I'll take Burroughs.

29:52.345 --> 29:53.636
I'll take that.

29:53.637 --> 29:55.637
Work? What do you mean, work?

29:56.512 --> 29:58.637
You were a surgeon, man.

30:00.119 --> 30:01.427
Wait, what time is it?

30:01.428 --> 30:02.993
Like, six.

30:02.994 --> 30:05.302
Haven't stayed up all
night since college.

30:05.303 --> 30:06.970
It's invigorating.

30:08.053 --> 30:09.970
[shudders]

30:11.260 --> 30:12.328
Here.

30:12.329 --> 30:15.386
- I already paid.
- No, no, it's fine.

30:15.387 --> 30:16.929
See you, man.

30:23.029 --> 30:24.253
Hi, Noah.

30:24.254 --> 30:27.312
So, I'm sorry, but I can't
let you on set today.

30:27.313 --> 30:28.678
What are you talking about?

30:28.679 --> 30:30.427
I guess Mr. Mann wants to limit

30:30.428 --> 30:32.651
the number of people on set
from this point forward.

30:32.652 --> 30:34.803
Just get on your radio
thing and call Mr. Mann

30:34.804 --> 30:36.624
and tell him to come
talk to me face-to-face.

30:36.625 --> 30:37.928
I can't. He's shooting.

30:37.929 --> 30:39.177
Yeah, I know. I-I got a rewrite

30:39.178 --> 30:40.678
for the scene he's shooting right now,

30:40.679 --> 30:41.761
so I need to get it to him.

30:41.762 --> 30:43.135
Oh, that's okay. He already has it.

30:43.136 --> 30:46.344
No, he... What? No. Wha... What?

30:46.345 --> 30:48.233
Yeah, the new pages
came out this morning.

30:48.234 --> 30:49.844
They're shooting them right now.

30:49.845 --> 30:53.386
[hypnotic, suspenseful music]

30:53.387 --> 30:55.469
Okay, you fucking call
him. Call him now.

30:55.470 --> 30:57.052
Call him on the radio now.

30:57.053 --> 30:58.844
Look at me and call...

30:58.845 --> 31:00.636
Call them on the fucking radio now!

31:00.637 --> 31:03.552
Call him now! Fucking call him.

31:03.553 --> 31:06.052
Jesus, this is the fucking rewrite here!

31:06.053 --> 31:07.470
Now get him out here!

31:10.239 --> 31:12.154
- _
- [easy listening music playing]

31:12.155 --> 31:13.446
[Margaret] Excuse me.

31:14.220 --> 31:17.511
This yolk is broken, I'd
like to send it back.

31:17.512 --> 31:19.052
Right away, ma'am.

31:19.053 --> 31:20.552
[exhales]

31:20.553 --> 31:22.427
Does this look moldy to you?

31:22.428 --> 31:23.844
- The napkin?
- You know,

31:23.845 --> 31:25.844
I'm very allergic to mold.

31:25.845 --> 31:27.219
What is that right there?

31:27.220 --> 31:28.594
Uh, it just looks like ketchup.

31:28.595 --> 31:30.636
Can't have mold in my lap.

31:30.637 --> 31:32.094
I'll break out in hives.

31:32.095 --> 31:34.383
Excuse me. Excuse me, please.

31:34.384 --> 31:36.552
Mom, is, is everything okay?

31:36.553 --> 31:38.164
I'm fine, why?

31:38.165 --> 31:40.091
You just seem a little tense.

31:40.092 --> 31:41.951
I'm very worried about you,

31:41.952 --> 31:43.557
I wanted to do something nice for you.

31:43.558 --> 31:45.594
Well, this is a very nice place.

31:45.595 --> 31:47.079
- Thank you.
- Do you think so?

31:47.080 --> 31:49.177
Shirley Divets said it
was the best restaurant

31:49.178 --> 31:51.886
in Los Angeles, but she
hasn't been out of Hyannis

31:51.887 --> 31:53.719
in 30 years, so what does she know?

31:53.720 --> 31:54.949
Excuse me.

31:58.303 --> 31:59.479
How's Dad?

32:00.506 --> 32:01.972
Why do you ask?

32:02.699 --> 32:04.010
Um...

32:04.011 --> 32:05.928
because I know he
doesn't usually like it

32:05.929 --> 32:07.386
when you're away.

32:07.387 --> 32:08.844
And you've been here for a while,

32:08.845 --> 32:10.552
so I'm just wondering how he's doing.

32:10.553 --> 32:12.457
[exhales sharply]

32:12.458 --> 32:15.212
That's actually something I
wanted to discuss with you.

32:17.720 --> 32:19.637
[exhales] I think it's time I go home.

32:21.720 --> 32:22.798
Oh.

32:23.565 --> 32:25.391
Well, I mean, if you think it's time.

32:25.392 --> 32:28.594
I hate the idea of
leaving you here alone

32:28.595 --> 32:31.135
in this extraordinarily
vulnerable state.

32:31.136 --> 32:33.636
Actually, I've been feeling
a little bit better lately.

32:33.637 --> 32:36.220
- So...
- But your father has dementia.

32:38.428 --> 32:39.719
What?

32:39.720 --> 32:42.719
And he's... lost all our money.

32:42.720 --> 32:44.928
- What?
- Excuse me.

32:44.929 --> 32:46.636
- What?
- Ma'am?

32:46.637 --> 32:49.177
This napkin is covered in mold.

32:49.178 --> 32:51.470
I'd like another. A clean one.

32:52.553 --> 32:54.292
[waiter] Of course, ma'am.

32:54.293 --> 32:55.511
I'm going to have a talk

32:55.512 --> 32:57.219
with Shirley Divets when I get back.

32:57.220 --> 33:00.011
Tell her she's too old to
be making recommendations.

33:00.012 --> 33:01.719
She thinks, just because she slept

33:01.720 --> 33:04.302
with Warren Beatty in '67,
she's an authority on every...

33:04.303 --> 33:06.678
[stammers] No, no, no, stop,
stop, stop. What... Okay.

33:06.679 --> 33:08.679
What, what do you mean Dad has dementia?

33:09.649 --> 33:12.246
- Alzheimer's, darling, I think.
- Well, how do you know?

33:12.247 --> 33:14.424
He gets confused, he forgets things.

33:14.425 --> 33:17.005
- So do I.
- It's not the same thing.

33:17.006 --> 33:19.047
The other day, he
couldn't find his keys.

33:19.048 --> 33:21.436
So what? I can never find my car keys.

33:21.437 --> 33:23.602
They were in his hand, Helen.

33:24.370 --> 33:25.615
It's just...

33:26.649 --> 33:28.259
he didn't know what they were.

33:28.260 --> 33:29.942
He didn't know what they were for.

33:35.261 --> 33:37.550
Uh, how long has this been going on?

33:38.211 --> 33:40.188
For a while. About a year.

33:40.189 --> 33:41.615
And you didn't tell me?

33:42.661 --> 33:45.025
You had a lot of things to worry about.

33:46.650 --> 33:48.644
Oh, my God, it never ends.

33:48.645 --> 33:50.260
[chuckling] I know.

33:50.261 --> 33:52.093
It feels like that
sometimes, doesn't it?

33:52.781 --> 33:54.511
And w-wait, who is with him now?

33:54.512 --> 33:57.313
- Is he alone?
- Of course not, Helen.

33:57.974 --> 33:59.377
We have a live-in nurse.

33:59.378 --> 34:01.939
Norene, and she's lovely.

34:01.940 --> 34:04.052
And she's very expensive,
I can't afford her.

34:04.557 --> 34:05.898
That's why I have to move back.

34:05.899 --> 34:07.761
[stammers] And, okay, what do you mean

34:07.762 --> 34:08.886
he lost all of your money?

34:08.887 --> 34:10.969
He gave a lot of it away to charity,

34:10.969 --> 34:12.302
which should have been my first clue

34:12.303 --> 34:14.083
there was something seriously wrong.

34:14.083 --> 34:17.083
And he made some idiotic investments.

34:17.083 --> 34:18.886
It's not all gone, mind you.

34:18.887 --> 34:20.511
We just have to be careful.

34:20.512 --> 34:23.010
If worst comes to worst,
we can sell the house.

34:23.011 --> 34:24.498
Oh, my God. Sell the house?

34:24.498 --> 34:26.511
I don't want to, either.

34:26.512 --> 34:28.177
But he needs a lot of care

34:28.178 --> 34:30.094
and I can't manage it on my own.

34:30.094 --> 34:32.245
The money has to come from somewhere.

34:32.246 --> 34:33.762
Unless...

34:37.199 --> 34:38.927
Oh, if you're asking me for money,

34:38.928 --> 34:40.949
I don't have any. Vik left
everything to his parents.

34:40.951 --> 34:43.194
Helen, I'm not asking you for money.

34:43.853 --> 34:46.094
I'm asking you to move back east

34:46.094 --> 34:48.020
and help me take care of him.

34:50.409 --> 34:52.469
It'd be a way to keep the house.

34:52.469 --> 34:54.302
No, but I... the kids...

34:54.303 --> 34:56.422
the kids are in, are in school here.

34:56.422 --> 34:58.048
There are schools on Long Island.

34:58.049 --> 35:00.344
Yes, but they've only
been here a few years.

35:00.345 --> 35:03.049
And to move them back this
soon would just be unfair.

35:03.050 --> 35:04.794
Life isn't fair.

35:05.587 --> 35:07.426
The sooner they understand that,

35:07.427 --> 35:09.487
the less disappointed they'll be.

35:11.095 --> 35:12.793
Just wait.

35:24.566 --> 35:26.667
Your father's dying, Helen.

35:28.220 --> 35:30.928
You give someone the
best years of your life

35:30.929 --> 35:32.969
while they fuck anything with a hole,

35:32.970 --> 35:34.969
and then you finally get
them back, and for what?

35:34.970 --> 35:38.261
The worst years of theirs.
It's definitely not fair.

35:40.621 --> 35:42.222
But I did get one thing from him.

35:44.074 --> 35:45.435
I got you.

35:47.714 --> 35:49.216
I got my girl.

35:53.095 --> 35:54.888
[somber music]

35:54.889 --> 35:57.468
[Eddie crying]

35:59.267 --> 36:00.470
Sierra?

36:01.553 --> 36:03.344
He won't eat.

36:03.345 --> 36:05.094
What do you mean?

36:05.095 --> 36:07.010
I don't, I don't know what's going on.

36:07.011 --> 36:09.219
I mean, first he would only take

36:09.220 --> 36:11.678
my right breast and then
only if we were bouncing.

36:11.679 --> 36:13.678
And now not at all.

36:13.679 --> 36:15.427
Here. [shushes] Eddie?

36:15.428 --> 36:16.761
Okay.

36:16.762 --> 36:18.344
Come on.

36:18.345 --> 36:19.844
Here you go, here.

36:19.845 --> 36:21.678
- [crying]
- [Margaret] Why are you trying

36:21.679 --> 36:23.761
to assault that baby with your breast?

36:23.762 --> 36:25.636
Mom, stop it.

36:25.637 --> 36:27.135
Can I... here, can I
hold him for a minute?

36:27.136 --> 36:28.719
- Yes.
- Okay.

36:28.720 --> 36:30.386
Here you go. Okay, sweetie.

36:30.387 --> 36:32.552
Hi. [shushes]

36:32.553 --> 36:33.844
Hi.

36:33.845 --> 36:35.969
Hi-hi-hi-hi-hi.

36:35.970 --> 36:37.302
Oh, he's hungry.

36:37.303 --> 36:39.052
Yeah, I know, so why won't he eat?

36:39.053 --> 36:41.052
Um, I don't know. Uh,
did you try a bottle?

36:41.053 --> 36:42.542
- Do you have a pump?
- No, no, no bottles.

36:42.543 --> 36:44.010
Oh, for God's sakes, give him a bottle.

36:44.011 --> 36:45.511
You're not living in a cave.

36:45.512 --> 36:47.628
My doula said it would
create nipple confusion,

36:47.629 --> 36:48.950
and then he's gonna reject my breast.

36:48.951 --> 36:50.571
- As he should.
- Okay.

36:50.572 --> 36:52.636
Um, Sierra, he needs to eat.

36:52.637 --> 36:54.136
So, why don't we just
get him some formula

36:54.137 --> 36:56.127
for now and then we'll,
we'll find you a pump.

36:56.128 --> 36:58.719
No, I can't, I can't give him formula.

36:58.720 --> 37:00.302
- Why not?
- Because it leads

37:00.303 --> 37:02.536
to a lifetime of obesity
and eating disorders.

37:02.537 --> 37:04.803
It's better to be plump and civilized

37:04.804 --> 37:06.260
- than raised like a wolf cub.
- Okay.

37:06.261 --> 37:08.094
That's really enough from you, okay?

37:08.095 --> 37:09.554
[crying continues]

37:09.555 --> 37:11.141
Sierra, when's the last time you slept?

37:11.142 --> 37:14.094
I don't know, I... a
day ago, two days ago.

37:14.095 --> 37:15.148
- I don't know.
- All right.

37:15.149 --> 37:17.594
Here's what's gonna happen.
You're gonna lie down

37:17.595 --> 37:19.092
in Stacey's room and you're gonna go out

37:19.093 --> 37:20.285
and get some formula and a bottle.

37:20.286 --> 37:22.077
- No, Helen.
- Yes, Sierra.

37:22.078 --> 37:24.260
One bottle is not gonna do any harm.

37:24.261 --> 37:26.010
He needs to eat and you need to sleep.

37:26.011 --> 37:27.594
So let's just...

37:27.595 --> 37:29.719
let's just fix these problems right now

37:29.720 --> 37:31.219
and then we'll sort out the rest, okay?

37:31.220 --> 37:33.094
- [exhales]
- [Eddie fussing]

37:33.095 --> 37:35.010
Go, just go ahead; it's
right down the hall.

37:35.011 --> 37:36.678
- On your right.
- Okay, thank you.

37:36.679 --> 37:38.511
Mm-hmm.

37:38.512 --> 37:41.260
[Eddie crying]

37:41.261 --> 37:43.302
You, too. Go.

37:43.303 --> 37:46.548
- That woman is a child.
- I know.

37:48.762 --> 37:50.803
Hi.

37:50.804 --> 37:52.804
[door opens]

37:53.929 --> 37:56.552
- Okay.
- [door closes]

37:56.553 --> 37:58.912
- [cries]
- Ah-ah-ah, none of that.

38:00.178 --> 38:01.477
- [stops crying]
- Thank you.

38:02.371 --> 38:03.877
- [babbles]
- Hmm.

38:05.637 --> 38:07.678
[gentle, hypnotic music]

38:07.679 --> 38:09.553
♪♪♪

38:12.880 --> 38:14.334
[softly] Nice work.

38:22.136 --> 38:24.303
You look just like your dad.

38:41.970 --> 38:44.095
[exhales slowly]

39:07.345 --> 39:09.230
[faint chatter on TV]

39:09.231 --> 39:10.761
Don't you guys have homework?

39:10.762 --> 39:12.161
[Trevor] We'll do it later.

39:12.162 --> 39:14.552
[man on TV] You have not met him yet.

39:14.553 --> 39:15.804
[man chuckles on TV]

39:17.095 --> 39:18.594
Is that what you like?

39:18.595 --> 39:20.511
What is this, The Maze?

39:20.512 --> 39:21.954
The Maze 2.

39:21.955 --> 39:24.177
- This time, it's even more personal.
- [snickers]

39:24.178 --> 39:26.553
It's um, yeah, the sequel.

39:28.340 --> 39:30.348
- What?
- How was your date?

39:30.349 --> 39:31.862
- That you went on?
- Uh, sorry, you know,

39:31.863 --> 39:32.928
he thought putting this on

39:32.929 --> 39:35.129
- would make you talk about it.
- With Sasha mother-freaking Mann?

39:35.130 --> 39:36.427
I... told him it was a dumb idea.

39:36.428 --> 39:37.803
It wasn't really a date, you guys.

39:37.804 --> 39:38.830
What is he like?

39:38.831 --> 39:40.344
- Yeah, are you gonna see him again?
- Yeah.

39:40.345 --> 39:41.483
When can I start

39:41.484 --> 39:43.180
telling people that Sasha Mann

39:43.181 --> 39:44.492
- is your boyfriend?
- You can't.

39:44.493 --> 39:46.594
And you can't tweet it or blog it

39:46.595 --> 39:48.511
- or any of that stuff.
- Don't worry, Mom, he won't.

39:48.512 --> 39:49.844
- It's a vlog. [chuckles]
- Okay.

39:49.845 --> 39:51.678
Anyway, I might be done with boyfriends

39:51.679 --> 39:53.158
- for a while.
- [Brooklyn] What?

39:54.398 --> 39:56.219
Well, I've had my share.

39:56.220 --> 39:57.597
They can be exhausting.

39:57.598 --> 39:59.427
I mean, do what you want,

39:59.428 --> 40:01.105
but you are way too hot not to have

40:01.106 --> 40:03.072
- any more boyfriends.
- Gross.

40:03.073 --> 40:04.386
- That's my mom.
- I'm serious.

40:04.387 --> 40:05.886
[Trevor] Stop.

40:05.887 --> 40:08.553
[phone ringing]

40:17.345 --> 40:19.050
- Hello?
- [Sasha] Hi.

40:19.051 --> 40:20.150
[on TV] Hi.

40:20.756 --> 40:21.978
Hi.

40:22.639 --> 40:25.803
Uh, uh, how's it going, Sasha... Mann?

40:25.804 --> 40:27.930
What are you doing right now?

40:27.931 --> 40:30.728
Uh, I'm at home. Why?

40:30.729 --> 40:33.216
Well, the thing is, uh,
ever since you came

40:33.217 --> 40:35.469
to my place and-and we spent
that evening together,

40:35.470 --> 40:38.427
I can't stop thinking
about my furniture.

40:38.428 --> 40:39.928
Your furniture?

40:39.929 --> 40:42.469
Yeah, I can't get it out of my head.

40:42.470 --> 40:45.511
I think you're right,
uh, I need more stuff.

40:45.512 --> 40:47.010
I was hoping you'd come by set

40:47.011 --> 40:48.344
and help me make some decisions.

40:48.345 --> 40:49.427
[Margaret] I'm sure you miss it.

40:49.428 --> 40:52.159
- If, if you're not too busy, that is.
- I know you have it on your mind.

40:52.160 --> 40:54.511
You remember how lovely the
summers are out there.

40:54.512 --> 40:55.803
- Don't you?
- Helen, are you there?

40:55.804 --> 40:57.302
Um, I have to deal with something here.

40:57.303 --> 40:58.803
I'll call you back.

40:58.804 --> 41:00.552
They've got a great high school there,

41:00.553 --> 41:02.678
Bridgehampton High. Huge building.

41:02.679 --> 41:04.249
- Very...
- Can I talk to you for a second?

41:08.887 --> 41:10.492
What are you doing? Are you telling him

41:10.493 --> 41:12.636
- we're moving?
- I'm just laying the groundwork.

41:12.637 --> 41:14.135
Please don't do that.

41:14.136 --> 41:15.260
Helen, you can't

41:15.261 --> 41:17.139
uproot them like you did last time.

41:17.140 --> 41:18.627
It's not healthy.

41:18.628 --> 41:21.831
Children have to be prepared
for traumatic events.

41:21.832 --> 41:23.761
I think what we should do

41:23.762 --> 41:25.690
tonight at dinner is talk about

41:25.691 --> 41:27.636
the East Coast in a general kind of way.

41:27.637 --> 41:29.177
You should say how much you miss it.

41:29.178 --> 41:30.969
I'll mention how glorious it is

41:30.970 --> 41:32.573
- this time of year.
- I'm going out.

41:39.303 --> 41:40.650
- [knocking]
- [Sasha] Yeah?

41:40.651 --> 41:42.762
Come on in.

41:45.803 --> 41:47.761
Oh, you came.

41:48.178 --> 41:49.686
I wasn't sure you would.

41:49.687 --> 41:52.717
Uh, yeah. I'm sorry, I
have... things going on.

41:52.718 --> 41:55.553
- I really appreciate you making time.
- Yeah.

41:57.303 --> 41:58.844
Please come on in.

41:58.845 --> 42:00.005
Sit down.

42:00.804 --> 42:02.684
- Um...
- [sighs]

42:02.685 --> 42:05.094
So you need some help
making some decisions?

42:05.095 --> 42:08.907
Yeah, um... thing is,

42:08.908 --> 42:11.886
I moved to Malibu because I was...

42:11.887 --> 42:13.886
grieving and I just needed to get away

42:13.887 --> 42:15.342
from the world and I thought,

42:15.343 --> 42:17.260
if I have nothing,

42:17.261 --> 42:19.050
then I'll have nothing to lose, right?

42:19.824 --> 42:21.243
But then the other night,

42:21.244 --> 42:24.905
uh, after you left, I realized
that time in my life is over.

42:24.906 --> 42:26.844
It-It's passed and I don't need

42:26.845 --> 42:29.006
to live like a monk anymore
to keep order in my head.

42:29.007 --> 42:31.544
I want to feel things again. So...

42:31.545 --> 42:33.133
I took you very seriously.

42:33.134 --> 42:35.000
And I hired a professional.

42:35.466 --> 42:37.886
Um... supposedly

42:38.601 --> 42:41.155
one of the best interior designers

42:41.156 --> 42:42.761
in all of Hollywood.

42:42.762 --> 42:44.761
- Um...
- The trouble is, look.

42:44.762 --> 42:47.095
I really don't like it.

42:49.220 --> 42:50.769
- No, I see what you mean.
- It's totally not

42:50.770 --> 42:52.135
- what I expected.
- It's chaotic.

42:52.136 --> 42:53.635
Yes, it is.

42:53.636 --> 42:55.552
- Um...
- It's too much.

42:55.553 --> 42:57.603
I was thinking...

42:57.604 --> 43:00.427
just, you know, things
with really clean,

43:00.428 --> 43:02.928
simple lines, like a modern
area rug there, maybe,

43:02.929 --> 43:06.011
or, um, or a Noguchi lamp there.

43:10.095 --> 43:11.489
What?

43:12.102 --> 43:14.144
I just had the most brilliant idea.

43:15.230 --> 43:16.516
Why don't you do it?

43:16.517 --> 43:19.106
What? No.

43:19.107 --> 43:20.594
Well, you know what you like

43:20.595 --> 43:21.928
and you obviously have great taste.

43:21.929 --> 43:23.828
Yeah, but I don't... I
have... I don't have...

43:23.829 --> 43:25.482
I'm... my...

43:25.483 --> 43:27.863
And we'd get to spend a
lot of time together.

43:30.845 --> 43:32.051
[quietly] Yeah.

43:33.261 --> 43:34.721
But why?

43:35.203 --> 43:36.803
[chuckles] What do you mean, why?

43:36.804 --> 43:39.469
I mean, there are tons of women.

43:39.470 --> 43:40.719
I'm sure you have tons of women.

43:40.720 --> 43:44.302
You know, famous women,
younger women, taller women

43:44.303 --> 43:46.511
that you-you can... You're...

43:46.512 --> 43:49.177
I'm having a very difficult time
believing that I'm your type.

43:49.178 --> 43:51.302
Uh, that's probably because you
don't have the faintest idea

43:51.303 --> 43:55.260
what my type is because
you categorically refuse

43:55.261 --> 43:56.970
to give me a chance.

43:58.095 --> 44:00.094
[knock on door]

44:00.095 --> 44:01.803
- Yes?
- [woman] Mr. Mann?

44:01.804 --> 44:03.863
- They need you on set.
- Just a second, please.

44:03.864 --> 44:06.511
Um, listen,

44:06.512 --> 44:08.594
I'm taking everybody out tonight

44:08.595 --> 44:10.177
for karaoke and drinks.

44:10.178 --> 44:12.608
Why don't you come, and
we can discuss this...

44:12.609 --> 44:14.010
Okay.

44:14.011 --> 44:15.775
Really?

44:15.776 --> 44:17.696
[laughs] Yes.

44:18.403 --> 44:21.010
[soft, ambient music]

44:21.011 --> 44:23.178
♪♪♪

44:25.095 --> 44:26.902
[Noah] Helen.

44:26.903 --> 44:28.761
Oh, um, hi.

44:28.762 --> 44:30.386
I just... Actually,
it's great you're here.

44:30.387 --> 44:31.844
I was, I was about to call you.

44:31.845 --> 44:33.241
You really need to talk to Whitney

44:33.242 --> 44:34.566
about this whole wedding thing.

44:34.567 --> 44:37.094
Um, uh, okay. What about it?

44:37.095 --> 44:40.320
Well, this-this kid, he's-he's-
he's using her for a green card.

44:40.321 --> 44:42.594
- He doesn't work, he doesn't...
- I don't think so.

44:42.595 --> 44:44.117
I mean, I think he loves her.

44:44.118 --> 44:46.136
No. It's too fast, and she is too young.

44:46.137 --> 44:48.427
And we're her parents.
We need to protect her.

44:48.428 --> 44:50.119
Uh, protect her from what?

44:50.120 --> 44:51.719
From making a big mistake.

44:51.720 --> 44:54.099
You want me to tell her
to call off her wedding?

44:54.100 --> 44:55.949
Yeah. I think you should.

44:57.178 --> 44:58.860
Why don't you do it?

44:58.861 --> 45:01.469
Because she doesn't listen
to me. She listens to you.

45:01.470 --> 45:03.052
- [Lisa] Rehearsal's up!
- Oh.

45:03.053 --> 45:04.635
Fuck, they need me for rehearsals.

45:04.636 --> 45:05.891
Will you talk to her?

45:05.892 --> 45:08.077
Uh... yeah, sure.

45:08.078 --> 45:10.469
Okay, thanks. Thanks for coming.

45:10.470 --> 45:11.887
It's really good of you.

45:14.281 --> 45:18.001
_

45:18.002 --> 45:20.052
[music playing]

45:20.053 --> 45:21.969
- [Sasha] Hey.
- Hi.

45:21.970 --> 45:23.928
- Hey.
- You're finished already.

45:23.929 --> 45:25.761
Yes. Done for the day.

45:25.762 --> 45:29.260
Um, can we have two negronis, please?

45:29.261 --> 45:32.261
And keep it open. A
lot of people coming.

45:33.261 --> 45:35.260
[sighs]

45:35.261 --> 45:36.696
So...

45:36.697 --> 45:39.302
- So...
- Have you thought about it?

45:39.303 --> 45:40.773
About what?

45:40.774 --> 45:42.302
Designing my house.

45:42.303 --> 45:43.803
[scoffs] I can't design

45:43.804 --> 45:45.678
- your house, Sasha.
- Why the hell not?

45:45.679 --> 45:47.540
Because I have too much going on.

45:47.541 --> 45:50.367
- Like what?
- Like what?

45:50.368 --> 45:51.613
Yes, like what?

45:51.614 --> 45:53.907
Like I just found out my
father has Alzheimer's.

45:53.908 --> 45:56.010
- And?
- And he's completely ruined

45:56.011 --> 45:58.357
- the family's finances.
- Poor you.

45:58.358 --> 46:01.045
My mother is a crazy,
narcissistic bitch.

46:01.046 --> 46:03.010
- Big deal.
- And my neighbor...

46:03.011 --> 46:05.219
- Mm-hmm.
- ...had a one-night stand

46:05.220 --> 46:06.636
with my boyfriend who died.

46:06.637 --> 46:07.719
[chuckles]

46:07.720 --> 46:09.421
Sorry, that's not funny.

46:09.422 --> 46:10.969
- No.
- No. Now she has his baby,

46:10.970 --> 46:12.302
and she wants me to take care of it.

46:12.303 --> 46:14.052
And I already have four kids of my own,

46:14.053 --> 46:15.634
the oldest of whom is getting married,

46:15.635 --> 46:18.143
and Noah wants me to convince
her to call off the wedding.

46:18.144 --> 46:19.552
- Why?
- Because, I don't know,

46:19.553 --> 46:20.709
he doesn't like the guy.

46:20.710 --> 46:22.148
Why doesn't Noah just
talk to her himself?

46:22.149 --> 46:25.275
Because they don't have
that kind of relationship.

46:25.276 --> 46:26.992
Helen, you don't have

46:26.993 --> 46:30.591
to set yourself on fire to
keep other people warm.

46:34.076 --> 46:36.117
I'm not really sure what that means.

46:36.118 --> 46:37.802
You are allowed to say no.

46:37.803 --> 46:39.858
Okay. No, I won't design your house.

46:39.859 --> 46:41.818
Oh, no, no, no, not to me.

46:41.819 --> 46:43.469
- Do you like gin?
- No.

46:43.470 --> 46:45.241
- Of course you do.
- [laughs]

46:45.242 --> 46:47.136
- Cheers.
- Thank you.

46:50.011 --> 46:51.928
Thank you.

46:51.929 --> 46:54.022
Can I ask you a question?

46:54.023 --> 46:55.177
Yeah, anything.

46:55.178 --> 46:57.242
Except if I'm in love with you.

46:57.243 --> 46:58.670
That's a secret.

47:03.178 --> 47:06.011
Uh, who did you lose?

47:07.178 --> 47:09.091
You said you were grieving.

47:10.845 --> 47:13.390
You really don't know
anything about me, do you?

47:14.973 --> 47:16.469
Not so much.

47:16.470 --> 47:17.719
You don't read the tabloids?

47:17.720 --> 47:19.474
Not since Noah went to prison.

47:20.820 --> 47:23.135
Um, her name was Lily,

47:23.579 --> 47:26.159
and she was my fiancée, and, um...

47:28.895 --> 47:31.386
We met as kids, and
we'd come up together.

47:31.387 --> 47:34.573
And, well, my success was awful for her.

47:34.574 --> 47:37.052
I didn't handle it well,
and-and she felt abandoned.

47:37.053 --> 47:39.361
And as I started working more,

47:39.362 --> 47:42.177
she started using more

47:42.178 --> 47:45.221
until, um...

47:46.847 --> 47:49.075
until she overdosed one day

47:50.101 --> 47:51.352
in our car.

47:51.720 --> 47:54.219
And I was the one who found her.

47:54.220 --> 47:56.386
The newspapers reported
it as a suicide, so...

47:56.387 --> 47:57.549
[Noah] Hey.

47:58.330 --> 47:59.427
Hey.

47:59.428 --> 48:01.511
- Hi.
- Hi.

48:01.512 --> 48:02.886
Good of you to join us.

48:02.887 --> 48:04.552
Yeah, thanks for doing this.

48:04.553 --> 48:05.882
It's a cute idea.

48:06.762 --> 48:08.052
- Something wrong?
- Yeah.

48:08.053 --> 48:09.886
Yeah, something is wrong, Sasha.

48:09.887 --> 48:12.177
I just, uh, got a call from my agents.

48:12.178 --> 48:14.600
They said you told the
studio that you want to...

48:14.601 --> 48:16.435
you want to rewrite the script.

48:17.815 --> 48:20.052
That's not exactly what I said,

48:20.053 --> 48:22.010
but I actually tried to
talk to you about this...

48:22.011 --> 48:23.511
Yeah, well, you got my
fucking attention now,

48:23.512 --> 48:25.427
so what's the problem?

48:25.428 --> 48:26.761
Do you think we should do this

48:26.762 --> 48:28.260
somewhere a bit more private, perhaps?

48:28.261 --> 48:29.787
Lead the way, Maestro.

48:29.788 --> 48:31.246
You gonna be all right?

48:31.247 --> 48:33.871
Yeah. Yeah.

48:33.872 --> 48:35.679
Okay.

48:41.095 --> 48:42.678
Hi.

48:42.679 --> 48:45.135
- You're the real Helen, right?
- Oh, yeah.

48:45.136 --> 48:46.803
And you're banging Sasha?

48:46.804 --> 48:48.885
- What?
- Well, everybody knows.

48:48.886 --> 48:50.177
Oh...

48:50.178 --> 48:52.298
You must really hate your ex-husband.

48:52.299 --> 48:54.910
- He seems like such a prick.
- Um...

48:56.037 --> 48:57.594
Good for you, honey.

48:57.595 --> 48:59.177
Get your revenge.

48:59.758 --> 49:02.469
- Cheers.
- I'm sorry, I have to go.

49:02.470 --> 49:04.552
[slow, melancholy music]

49:04.553 --> 49:07.135
♪♪♪

49:07.136 --> 49:08.594
You're still up?

49:08.595 --> 49:10.287
Yeah, I can't sleep.

49:11.387 --> 49:14.405
So, why does Stacey have
to sleep with Grandma?

49:14.406 --> 49:17.678
Because Sierra and Eddie are
in Stacey's room tonight.

49:17.679 --> 49:19.969
Okay, fine. Do we have any LaCroix?

49:19.970 --> 49:21.386
Brooklyn's thirsty.

49:21.387 --> 49:23.427
Check the back?

49:23.428 --> 49:24.761
Score.

49:24.762 --> 49:26.260
Brooklyn's staying over?

49:26.261 --> 49:27.727
Uh, yeah.

49:28.954 --> 49:30.758
I'm such a cool mom.

49:31.990 --> 49:33.519
You are a cool mom.

49:34.220 --> 49:35.427
Thanks.

49:35.428 --> 49:36.800
No, no, really.

49:37.287 --> 49:38.969
Just between you and me,

49:38.970 --> 49:40.828
could have been so much worse.

49:41.540 --> 49:43.510
- Thank you.
- So, how long

49:43.511 --> 49:45.649
- is Sierra staying with us?
- I don't know.

49:46.303 --> 49:47.344
Grandma?

49:47.345 --> 49:49.260
I don't know that, either.

49:49.261 --> 49:51.782
I think they're all gonna stay
until they're ready to leave.

49:53.011 --> 49:54.855
Okay, yeah, that's fine.

49:54.856 --> 49:58.678
Then I will be booking an extra
session with my therapist.

49:59.415 --> 50:00.819
You don't have a therapist.

50:00.820 --> 50:02.386
Yeah, but I need one.

50:02.387 --> 50:04.282
- Good night, Mom.
- Good night.

50:12.587 --> 50:14.671
[knocking on door]

50:19.387 --> 50:21.178
[knocking continues]

50:24.305 --> 50:25.456
What?!

50:25.457 --> 50:26.794
- Where is he?
- Who?

50:26.795 --> 50:28.678
I know he's here. Where
the fuck is he? Sasha!

50:28.679 --> 50:29.886
- Oh, God.
- Sasha!

50:29.887 --> 50:31.260
Shut up.

50:31.261 --> 50:33.177
You are wasted.

50:33.178 --> 50:34.719
Go home. Do you want the kids

50:34.720 --> 50:36.678
- to see you like this?
- He's fucking using you, Helen.

50:37.260 --> 50:39.388
He's using you to get to me.

50:39.389 --> 50:41.260
He's playing me, so he wants to fuck you

50:41.261 --> 50:43.010
so he feels closer to me.

50:43.011 --> 50:45.382
Can't you see how pathetic that is?

50:45.383 --> 50:46.988
[quiet, atmospheric music]

50:46.989 --> 50:49.567
It's fucking freezing out
here. Can I just come in?

50:49.568 --> 50:51.719
- No.
- Just... come on.

50:51.720 --> 50:53.006
- No.
- Seriously.

50:53.007 --> 50:54.886
Yeah. Go home.

50:54.887 --> 50:56.378
Don't drive. Take an Uber.

50:56.379 --> 50:59.010
I don't care what you do. Just go.

50:59.011 --> 51:00.407
Good night.

51:00.408 --> 51:02.886
Helen, come...

51:02.887 --> 51:04.928
Helen? Helen, I'll call a guy.

51:04.929 --> 51:06.844
- Just let me in.
- [knocking on door]

51:06.845 --> 51:08.719
Come on, Helen.

51:08.720 --> 51:11.719
Helen, come on!

51:11.720 --> 51:13.693
- [snickers]
- Helen!

51:13.694 --> 51:15.779
♪♪♪

51:20.637 --> 51:23.872
[line ringing]

51:23.873 --> 51:25.260
[Sasha] Hello?

51:25.261 --> 51:26.387
Hi.

51:28.633 --> 51:29.886
Are you mad?

51:29.887 --> 51:31.260
No, not mad.

51:31.261 --> 51:33.511
Um, just confused.

51:33.512 --> 51:36.969
I-I told you the worst thing
that ever happened to me,

51:36.970 --> 51:39.761
and you just... disappeared.

51:39.762 --> 51:41.303
I know. I'm sorry.

51:43.118 --> 51:44.511
I'm really sorry.

51:44.512 --> 51:46.378
D-Do you want to keep talking?

51:46.379 --> 51:48.272
No, not really.

51:50.804 --> 51:53.166
Do you want to do something else?

51:57.387 --> 51:59.844
[both moaning]

51:59.845 --> 52:01.803
- Shh.
- [whispering] What?

52:01.804 --> 52:03.469
- [whispering] Shh, quiet.
- Why?

52:03.470 --> 52:05.261
Because I have a house full of people.

52:06.470 --> 52:07.761
Who's here?

52:07.762 --> 52:10.552
Um... my daughter.

52:10.553 --> 52:11.761
Mm-hmm.

52:11.762 --> 52:14.803
My son.

52:14.804 --> 52:17.552
- His boyfriend.
- [laughs]

52:17.553 --> 52:19.552
Uh, my mother.

52:19.553 --> 52:21.469
You got the whole family.

52:21.470 --> 52:22.803
- And my neighbor.
- [laughing]

52:22.804 --> 52:24.803
Shh. And her baby.

52:24.804 --> 52:27.844
[both laughing]

52:27.845 --> 52:29.929
It's okay.

52:41.470 --> 52:43.803
Mmm.

52:43.804 --> 52:46.052
- Helen.
- Hmm?

52:46.053 --> 52:49.761
- Design my house.
- [chuckles]

52:49.762 --> 52:52.285
Give me a lamp.

52:52.286 --> 52:54.552
Just one room, please.

52:54.553 --> 52:55.928
[chuckling]

52:55.929 --> 52:57.344
[muffled] Just one room.

52:57.345 --> 52:59.177
Just one tiny, little room.

52:59.178 --> 53:01.761
Helen, just give me a rug.

53:01.762 --> 53:04.819
Can-can you give me a rug, please?

53:04.820 --> 53:06.386
Give me a rug.

53:06.387 --> 53:07.970
Can you give me a...?

53:16.345 --> 53:17.844
- [Margaret] Good morning.
- Morning.

53:17.845 --> 53:20.344
- Coffee?
- Sure.

53:20.345 --> 53:21.835
How'd you sleep?

53:22.735 --> 53:24.197
Really well, thanks.

53:25.377 --> 53:28.427
I think I can get the kids enrolled

53:28.428 --> 53:30.427
in the Bridgehampton high
school for the spring semester,

53:30.428 --> 53:32.515
so if you put this house on
the market next month...

53:32.516 --> 53:34.422
Mom, I'm not moving back.

53:34.423 --> 53:35.836
What?

53:37.317 --> 53:38.802
I have a life here.

53:38.803 --> 53:40.283
I'll help you and Dad out

53:40.284 --> 53:41.328
as much as I can,

53:41.329 --> 53:42.772
but I-I'm not moving home.

53:43.491 --> 53:45.340
What am I supposed to do?

53:46.648 --> 53:48.087
You will figure it out.

53:48.668 --> 53:50.353
What's gotten into you?

53:50.354 --> 53:51.779
[Sasha] Good morning.

53:52.553 --> 53:54.803
[slow, quiet music]

53:54.804 --> 53:56.529
♪♪♪

53:56.845 --> 53:58.510
- Hey.
- Hi.

53:59.541 --> 54:01.373
You must be Margaret. I'm Sasha.

54:01.374 --> 54:04.166
- I...
- Pleasure to meet you.

54:04.167 --> 54:05.761
I'd actually love a cup of coffee,

54:05.762 --> 54:07.355
if it's not too much trouble.

54:09.328 --> 54:11.327
Thank you.

54:11.328 --> 54:14.121
♪♪♪

54:17.592 --> 54:20.841
_

54:29.279 --> 54:30.844
[Marcy Playground's "Sex
and Candy" playing]

54:30.845 --> 54:32.886
♪ Like double cherry pie ♪

54:32.887 --> 54:36.594
♪ Yeah, there she was ♪

54:36.595 --> 54:41.135
♪ Like disco superfly ♪

54:41.136 --> 54:46.220
- [children chattering playfully]
- ♪ I smell sex and candy here ♪

54:47.512 --> 54:52.220
♪ Who's that lounging in my chair? ♪

54:53.178 --> 54:54.386
♪ Who's that... ♪

54:54.387 --> 54:55.719
[bartender] Those your kids?

54:56.650 --> 54:57.762
No.

54:59.095 --> 55:01.524
Do I look like the kind of
person who would have kids?

55:01.525 --> 55:03.469
It isn't a crime.

55:03.470 --> 55:04.879
It should be.

55:04.880 --> 55:07.010
♪ This surely is a dream... ♪

55:07.611 --> 55:08.831
No, they're just...

55:09.638 --> 55:12.302
some refugee kids that I met in Senegal.

55:12.303 --> 55:13.487
Oh, yeah?

55:13.488 --> 55:15.135
What were you doing out there?

55:15.136 --> 55:16.595
I'm a coastal engineer.

55:17.629 --> 55:19.094
How's that going?

55:19.095 --> 55:20.546
Not well.

55:21.136 --> 55:24.094
♪ And I had too much caffeine ♪

55:24.095 --> 55:26.969
♪ And I was thinkin' 'bout myself... ♪

55:26.970 --> 55:28.151
[receiver beeps]

55:28.152 --> 55:30.172
- Have a good one.
- Thanks for the tip, Jim.

55:30.173 --> 55:32.719
♪ In platform double suede ♪

55:32.720 --> 55:35.844
♪ Yeah, there she was... ♪

55:35.845 --> 55:37.554
Can I ask you a question?

55:37.555 --> 55:39.060
Shoot.

55:39.061 --> 55:40.820
What's with the electricity out here?

55:40.821 --> 55:42.844
Is the grid completely off?

55:42.845 --> 55:45.145
No. Just ever since the last hurricane,

55:45.146 --> 55:46.554
they only turn it on
between nine and five.

55:46.555 --> 55:48.678
We got our own battery bank, though.

55:48.679 --> 55:51.135
This place used to be so beautiful.

55:51.136 --> 55:52.761
Yeah, well, there aren't enough of us

55:52.762 --> 55:54.065
out here to matter anymore.

55:54.066 --> 55:55.564
We can't afford those wind turbines

55:55.565 --> 55:57.434
they got out in East Hampton, so...

55:57.435 --> 55:58.605
Right.

56:05.061 --> 56:06.512
[bartender] You here for work?

56:08.126 --> 56:09.552
I am.

56:09.553 --> 56:11.220
Oh.

56:12.646 --> 56:14.194
How much do I owe you?

56:15.294 --> 56:16.748
It's on the house.

56:18.439 --> 56:21.420
I haven't seen a face like
yours out here in a while.

56:22.953 --> 56:24.387
I like it.

56:25.887 --> 56:27.928
[tense music]

56:27.929 --> 56:31.095
[both moaning]

56:32.220 --> 56:34.261
Yeah.

56:36.552 --> 56:39.714
- [gasps] Tighter.
- What?

56:39.715 --> 56:40.761
[Joanie grunts]

56:40.762 --> 56:42.761
- Better?
- [grunts, inhales sharply]

56:42.762 --> 56:44.595
- What?
- [panting]

56:46.702 --> 56:48.195
What's up?

56:49.095 --> 56:50.386
It's not working for me.

56:50.387 --> 56:51.552
What the fuck do you want?

56:57.052 --> 56:59.134
You are one sick bitch.

56:59.135 --> 57:01.261
♪♪♪

57:25.887 --> 57:27.631
[Joanie] Stop.

57:27.632 --> 57:29.387
[gasps]

57:30.303 --> 57:32.135
[moaning]

57:32.136 --> 57:33.984
- [bartender] Oh, yeah.
- [Joanie moans]

